# Production deployment (required)

Drive + Peace is deployed to **GitHub Pages** on every push to `main`.

**Production URL:** https://mct-dev.github.io/drive-and-peace/

## One-time prerequisite

If deploy fails with *"Ensure GitHub Pages has been enabled"*, the repo admin must:

1. Open https://github.com/mct-dev/drive-and-peace/settings/pages
2. Set **Source** to **GitHub Actions**
3. Re-run the deploy workflow on `main`

See `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md` for details.

## End-of-task checklist

Before finishing any chunk of work, complete all of the following:

1. **Verify locally**
   - `npm test`
   - `npm run build`

2. **Ship to production**
   - Commit and push your branch.
   - Merge the change into `main` (open/update PR and merge, or push directly to `main` when appropriate).
   - Confirm the **Deploy to GitHub Pages** workflow succeeds on `main` (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`).
   - The workflow must pass all three jobs: **build**, **deploy**, and **verify**.

3. **Verify production after deploy (required)**
   - Run `npm run verify:deploy` after the workflow completes, or wait for the workflow **verify** job to pass.
   - Confirm HTTP 200 from https://mct-dev.github.io/drive-and-peace/
   - Confirm the page contains `Drive + Peace` (the verify script checks this).
   - If verification fails, do **not** mark the task complete. Diagnose, fix, redeploy, and re-verify.
   - A 404 means GitHub Pages is not enabled or the deploy job failed — check Actions logs first.

4. **Final response must include a test link**
   - Always end your summary with a **Live preview** section.
   - Include the production URL: https://mct-dev.github.io/drive-and-peace/
   - Only claim the site is live if `npm run verify:deploy` (or the workflow verify job) passed.
   - If deployment or verification is still running, say so explicitly.
   - Do not mark work complete without attempting deployment **and** verification.

## Notes

- Vite `base` is `/drive-and-peace/` for GitHub Pages subpath hosting.
- React Router uses `basename={import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`.
- `dist/404.html` is generated at build time for SPA deep-link support on GitHub Pages.
- Data remains local-only in the browser; production is a static frontend only.
- Verification script: `scripts/verify-production.mjs` (also run via `npm run verify:deploy`).
